\lim\limits_{n\to\infty} \frac{n(n+1)(n+2)\dots(n+r)}{n^{r+1}}
r
1
\lim\limits_{n\to\infty} n(n+1)(n+2)\dots(n+r)=\lim\limits_{n\to\infty}{n^{r+1}}
\lim\limits_{n\to\infty} \left[n(n+1)(n+2)\dots(n+r)\right]-{n^{r+1}}=0
\left[n(n+1)(n+2)\dots(n+r)\right]-{n^{r+1}}=n^r(1+2+\dots+n)+n^{r-1}(1.2+1.3+\dots+(r-1)r)+\dots+r!
\lim\limits_{n\to\infty}n^r(1+2+\dots+n)+n^{r-1}(1.2+1.3+\dots+(r-1)r)+\dots+r!
L :=\lim_{n\rightarrow \infty} A_n = \lim_{n\rightarrow\infty} B_n \implies \lim_{n\rightarrow\infty} A_n - B_n = 0
